{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts"},"abstract":[{"text":"Some components can be used for ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"layouts","type":"text"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"level":3,"text":"Colored Surface","type":"heading","anchor":"Colored-Surface"},{"tabs":[{"title":"Orange","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Orange Business Tools","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_OrangeBusinessTools"}]}]},{"title":"Sosh","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Sosh","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Wireframe","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Wireframe","type":"image"}]}]}],"type":"tabNavigator"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Mono","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" suffix (for instance ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"colorBgDefaultEnabledMono"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" of ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"text":"How it works","type":"heading","anchor":"How-it-works","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the color, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsUseMonochrome"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsOnColoredSurface"},{"text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"text":"How to use","type":"heading","anchor":"How-to-use","level":4},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"onStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.onStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.contentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.contentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.onStatusPositiveEmphasized)"]},{"text":"Debuging contrast ratios","type":"heading","anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is for example the case for France with the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", also named “RGAA”."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components like "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used on "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratio.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratio.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Divider","level":3,"text":"Divider","type":"heading"},{"anchor":"How-it-works","level":4,"text":"How it works","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSHorizontalDivider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":": to separate elements stacked vertically (e.g. in ","type":"text"},{"code":"VStack","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSVerticalDivider"},{"type":"text","text":": to separate elements stacked horizontally (e.g. in `HStack)"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSDividerColor"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Horizontal","level":5,"text":"Horizontal","type":"heading"},{"tabs":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Orange"}]}],"title":"Orange"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_OrangeBusinessTools"}]}],"title":"Orange Business Tools"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Sosh","type":"image"}]}],"title":"Sosh"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_Wireframe"}]}],"title":"Wireframe"}],"type":"tabNavigator"},{"anchor":"Vertical","level":5,"text":"Vertical","type":"heading"},{"tabs":[{"title":"Orange","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"title":"Orange Business Tools","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_verticalDivider_OrangeBusinessTools","type":"image"}]}]},{"title":"Sosh","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Sosh"}]}]},{"title":"Wireframe","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Wireframe","type":"image"}]}]}],"type":"tabNavigator"},{"anchor":"How-to-use","level":4,"text":"How to use","type":"heading"},{"tabs":[{"title":"SwiftUI","content":[{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello world!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello world!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"}]},{"title":"UIKit (experimental)","content":[{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import OUDSComponentsUIKit","    ","\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","OUDSUIKit.createVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    ","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","OUDSUIKit.createHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)"]}]}],"type":"tabNavigator"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"metadata":{"title":"Layouts","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png"}],"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"article","references":{"component_coloredSurface_Wireframe":{"alt":"A colored surface with text, button and link in light and dark mode with Wireframe theme","identifier":"component_coloredSurface_Wireframe","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/OUDSComponents\/component_coloredSurface_Wireframe.png"}],"type":"image"},"component_horizontalDivider_OrangeBusinessTools":{"identifier":"component_horizontalDivider_OrangeBusinessTools","alt":"An horizontal divider in light and dark mode with Orange Business Tools theme","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/OUDSComponents\/component_horizontalDivider_OrangeBusinessTools.png"}],"type":"image"},"component_verticalDivider_Orange":{"alt":"An vertical divider in light and dark mode with Orange theme","identifier":"component_verticalDivider_Orange","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/OUDSComponents\/component_verticalDi